  "texts": [
    "3) Comparison of Tasks: The bar chart illustrates the relationship between various task types and specific error types encountered in data analysis and visualization using large models.",
    "The tasks for the tests are shown in Table I.For Correlation Analysis, the primary errors are Data Transformation Issues and Data Binding Issues, with occasional Syntax Errors.",
    "In Trend Analysis, the most frequent issues are Data Transformation Issues, indicating challenges in converting data formats or structures, and Data Binding Issues, which point to problems in linking data with visualization elements.Segmentation Analysis also suffers from Data Transformation Issues and Data Binding Issues.",
    "For Predictive Modeling, significant errors include Serialization Issues, suggesting difficulties in data serialization processes, along with Data Binding Issues.Variance Analysis encounters substantial Unfamiliar Dataset issues, highlighting challenges in working with new or unexpected data, and occasional Serialization Issues.",
    "Cluster Analysis is predominantly affected by Unfamiliar Dataset issues, reflecting problems with novel dataset, and some Data Transformation Issues.Aggregation Analysis shows minimal errors with an even distribution across different types, while Distribution Analysis is mainly affected by Data Binding Issues."
  ]
}